[ctns_make id='QF-QuadraticFormula']

    [ctns_front]
The Quadratic Formula
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
Given a quadratic function in general form

$|ax^2 + bx + c = 0,|$

then the solutions are
$|x=\frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}|$
    [/ctns_back]

    [ctns_backspeak]
The solution to the quadratic formula is the value

x equals negative b -- plus or minus the square root of b-squared minus 4--a--c -- all divided by 2--a.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

[/ctns_make]
